https://leetcode.com/problems/contiguous-array/description/

QUESTION:
Input: nums = [0,1,1,1,1,1,0,0,0]
Output: 6
Explanation: [1,1,1,0,0,0] is the longest contiguous subarray with equal number of 0 and 1.

SOLUTION:
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
TIME COMPLEXITY:O(n)
SPACE COMPLEXITY:O(n)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1)Create a hashmap(one for rsum and one for index value)
2)if the value is 1 add else subtract
3)if map doesnt have the rsum value then that is the max value in the present sequence
4)but if map contains the rsum value then you have to check which is the max value,the already existing max or i-rsum(index)
5)return the max
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
CODE:
class Solution {
    public int findMaxLength(int[] nums) {
        if(nums==null || nums.length<=1)return 0;
        HashMap<Integer,Integer>map=new HashMap<>();
        int rsum=0;
        int max=0;
        map.put(0,-1);
        for(int i=0;i<nums.length;i++){
            if(nums[i]==1)rsum+=1;
            if(nums[i]==0)rsum-=1;
            if(!map.containsKey(rsum)){
                map.put(rsum,i);
            }else{
                max=Math.max(max,i-map.get(rsum));
            }
        }
        return max;
    }
}
